author: William Morris
content: "Worthy work carries with it the hope of pleasure in rest, the hope of the\
  \ pleasure in our using what it makes, and the hope of pleasure in our daily creative\
  \ skill. All other work but this is worthless; it is slaves' work \u2014 mere toiling\
  \ to live, that we may live to toil."
